    <div class="prose" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-12);">
      <p>Transport in County Kerry involves a number of organisations with overlapping responsibilities: Kerry County Council, the National Transport Authority, Transport Infrastructure Ireland, Iarnród Éireann, Bus Éireann, and local operators such as the Rural Transport Programme. Understanding who is responsible for what is an essential first step for any representative looking to make progress on a specific issue.</p>
      <p>The materials on this page are designed to be practically useful — concise enough to read quickly, and specific enough to be actionable in a council or committee context.</p>
    </div>

